gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Lakers 130, Clippers 125
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by LeBron James 35 points (13-19 FG), 11 rebounds and seven assists, the Lakers defeated the Clippers, 130-125, in overtime. Anthony Davis (27 points, 10 rebounds) and DAngelo Russell (27 points, six assists) added a combined 54 points for the Lakers in the victory, while Kawhi Leonard (38 points, six rebounds, five assists) and Kawhi Leonard (35 points, six rebounds) combined for 73 points for the Clippers in the losing effort. The Lakers improve to 3-2 on the season, while the Clippers fall to 3-2.
